<entry>
  <title type="html"><![CDATA[Code highlighting in a Jekyll-based blog]]></title>
  <link>http://valera-rozuvan.github.io/nintoku/jekyll/code/highlighting/blog/code-highlighting-jekyll-based-blog</link>
  <id>http://valera-rozuvan.github.io/nintoku/jekyll/code/highlighting/blog/code-highlighting-jekyll-based-blog</id>
  <published>2013-12-17T18:08:25Z</published>
  <updated>2013-12-17T18:08:25Z</updated>
  <author>
    <name>Valera Rozuvan</name>
    <uri>http://valera-rozuvan.github.io/nintoku</uri>
    <email>valera.rozuvan@gmail.com</email>
  </author>
  <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;It turns out that Jekyll has access to a very powerful code highlighting system
&lt;a href=&quot;http://pygments.org/&quot;&gt;pygments&lt;/a&gt;. There is a huge number of &lt;a href=&quot;http://pygments.org/docs/lexers/&quot;&gt;lexers&lt;/a&gt;
that define the rules for highlighting for many, many languages.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To use it, you surround your code block like so&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;%&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;highlight&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;lexer_name&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;%&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;

        &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;...&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;code&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;goes&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;here&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;...&lt;/span&gt;

    &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;%&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;endhighlight&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;%&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;lexer_name&lt;/strong&gt; is a short name for a programming language.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;NOTE: To enable syntax highlighting, please set the &lt;em&gt;pygments&lt;/em&gt; variable to
&lt;em&gt;true&lt;/em&gt; in the &lt;code&gt;_config.yml&lt;/code&gt; configuration file (see
&lt;a href=&quot;http://jekyllrb.com/docs/templates/&quot;&gt;reference&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://valera-rozuvan.github.io/nintoku/jekyll/code/highlighting/blog/code-highlighting-jekyll-based-blog&quot;&gt;Code highlighting in a Jekyll-based blog&lt;/a&gt; was originally published by Valera Rozuvan at &lt;a href=&quot;http://valera-rozuvan.github.io/nintoku&quot;&gt;Nintoku&lt;/a&gt; on December 17, 2013.&lt;/p&gt;</content>
</entry>


<entry>
  <title type="html"><![CDATA[Jasmine toBeCloseTo() matcher]]></title>
  <link>http://valera-rozuvan.github.io/nintoku/jasmine/jasmine-tobecloseto-matcher</link>
  <id>http://valera-rozuvan.github.io/nintoku/jasmine/jasmine-tobecloseto-matcher</id>
  <published>2013-12-16T17:50:56Z</published>
  <updated>2013-12-16T17:50:56Z</updated>
  <author>
    <name>Valera Rozuvan</name>
    <uri>http://valera-rozuvan.github.io/nintoku</uri>
    <email>valera.rozuvan@gmail.com</email>
  </author>
  <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Today I was faced with a problem of checking that a number was really close
to another number, but not necessarily equal to it.
&lt;a href=&quot;http://pivotal.github.com/jasmine/&quot;&gt;Jasmine&lt;/a&gt; has a really nifty
matcher &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/pivotal/jasmine/blob/master/src/core/matchers/toBeCloseTo.js&quot;&gt;toBeCloseTo()&lt;/a&gt;
just for this case. See the code below.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;js+genshi&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nx&quot;&gt;getJasmineRequireObj&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;().&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nx&quot;&gt;toBeCloseTo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;kd&quot;&gt;function&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;

    &lt;span class=&quot;kd&quot;&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nx&quot;&gt;toBeCloseTo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span class=&quot;nx&quot;&gt;compare&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;kd&quot;&gt;function&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nx&quot;&gt;actual&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nx&quot;&gt;expected&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nx&quot;&gt;precision&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
                &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nx&quot;&gt;precision&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;!==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
                    &lt;span class=&quot;nx&quot;&gt;precision&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nx&quot;&gt;precision&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;
                &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
                    &lt;span class=&quot;nx&quot;&gt;pass&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nx&quot;&gt;abs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nx&quot;&gt;expected&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nx&quot;&gt;actual&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nx&quot;&gt;pow&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nx&quot;&gt;precision&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
                &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;};&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;};&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;

    &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nx&quot;&gt;toBeCloseTo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;};&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


  &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://valera-rozuvan.github.io/nintoku/jasmine/jasmine-tobecloseto-matcher&quot;&gt;Jasmine toBeCloseTo() matcher&lt;/a&gt; was originally published by Valera Rozuvan at &lt;a href=&quot;http://valera-rozuvan.github.io/nintoku&quot;&gt;Nintoku&lt;/a&gt; on December 16, 2013.&lt;/p&gt;</content>
</entry>


